<isis lang="en">
    <stitle>9 SPEED TRANSMISSIONS EATON RT-8609 SERIES - INSTALL - Shifter Housing</stitle>
    <svcsection/>
    <svcproc svcproctype="IDcomponent" graphiccount="3">
        <title>Shifter Housing</title>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Place all three mainshaft sliding clutches in the neutral position (
                <hotlnk xrefid="f13029m9">Figure 229</hotlnk>). Install shifter housing gasket in position.
            </para>
            <figure id="f13029m9" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic id="g13029m9" filename="../figg13/G13029M9.webp" type="webp"/>
                <caption>Figure 229. Place Mainshaft Sliding Clutches in Neutral Position</caption>
            </figure>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">With all three shift yokes in the neutral position, install the shifter housing assembly on
                the case, fitting the shift yokes into the slots of the corresponding sliding clutches (
                <hotlnk xrefid="f13029n0">Figure 230</hotlnk>).
            </para>
            <figure id="f13029n0" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic id="g13029n0" filename="../figg13/G13029N0.webp" type="webp"/>
                <caption>Figure 230. Install Shifter Housing Assembly on Case</caption>
            </figure>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Apply Loctite 242 or equivalent to the bolt threads. Install thirteen bolts in shifter
                housing and tighten to 35 to 45 ft-lbs. (47 to 61 N&#8226;m) (
                <hotlnk xrefid="f13029n1">Figure 231</hotlnk>).
            </para>
            <figure id="f13029n1" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic id="g13029n1" filename="../figg13/G13029N1.webp" type="webp"/>
                <caption>Figure 231. Install Bolts in Shifter Housing and Tighten</caption>
            </figure>
            <specpara>
                <note>
                    <para>There are two sizes of bolts. The 1-1/2 inch bolts are used with lifting eyes. Their position
                        on the shifter housing is shown in
                        <hotlnk document="s13029_33.xml" xrefid="f1302981">Figure 81</hotlnk>.
                    </para>
                </note>
            </specpara>
        </step1>
    </svcproc>
